es of the European countryside influenced metropolitan literary culture in fundamental ways.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aExperimental poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLinguistic minoritieszEuropevCross-cultural studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030018515740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019056440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300190564423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300190564/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY